History:
First generation of computers
- MCU micro controllers
- single process
- relays or vacuum tubes

Transistor Revolution
- Core memory: magnetic memory core

Third generation:
- multics -> unix
- Multiprogrammed
- spooling -> Simultananous prepheral operation on line
- Daemon: Disk arbitration and execution monitor

fourth generation:
- Modern PCs

___________________________________________
OS: (Kernal)
- resource manager
- Abstract machine (Drivers)


Tools:
- Putty or ssh
- Kernel
- Config file -> .config
- make menuconfig (check general and set your name so you know you get the right kernel loaded)
- make TAGS
- Linux cross refrencer LXR for non VIM and emacs
- Git
- Screen
- gdb
- qemu (use only 4 threads)

